track_notes: A hike on the quiet side of Serfaus: the transit from Pezid is in general a beautiful ridge hike along a grassy slope on the southern side and a impressive cliff on the northern side. The first short part down from the Pezid summit to the Pezidsattel saddle is narrow and slippery - a pure contrast to the access road on the other side. The hike along the Riefenkopf is well viable and beautiful, with a steep descent to the Riefenjoch junction. There is a shepherd hut, a good place for a break. The ascent to Hinterer Heuberg is a straight and quite simple trail along the ridge of this secluded and peaceful summit. There were sheep on the summit, but the AZ is big enough to keep some distance to the animals and their dung. Lots of aconite over all the summit.

Doing both Pezid and Hinterer Heuberg will probably prevent you from getting back to the Lazid gondola top station in time, so the more likely variant is descending directly to Komperdell/Alpkopf. There is only one small trail to the valley, but it is a masterpiece how it had been designed into this very steep mountain scenery. The descent takes time, so take care to not miss the last gondola down. The trail is easy T2 as soon as you have reached the hut nearby the large boulder in the valley nearby the mountain streams.
track_title: Descent via Riefenjoch to the Alpkopfbahn/Komperdell station
